title: Production of be-7, Na-22, Na-24 and Mg-28 by Irradiation of Al-27 with 52 MeV Deuterons and 104 MeV Alpha Particles

x4freetext: Production of be-7, Na-22, Na-24 and Mg-28 by
Irradiation of Al-27 with 52 MeV Deuterons and 104 MeV
Alpha Particles
. Zyklotron Laboratorium

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Zeitschrift fuer Physik, Vol.233, p.170 (1970)

x4freetext: Numerical Data.
Primary Beam-Energy is 52 MeV For Deuterons and 104 MeV
For Alpha-Particles, Current was About 1 Microamp.
Energy Degradation in the Stack was Calculated
According to C.F.Williamson Et Al., Cea-R3042(1966).
Shorter-Lived Activities were Counted a Few Days,
Longer-Lived a Few Weeks After Irradiation.
The Charge Collected by the Faraday Cup was Corrected
For the Dark Current Due to the Water Cooling of the
Target and the Radio Frequency Pick Up. Corrections
For the Energy Spread in the Target Foils Which were
Small in Comparison to the Energy Uncertainty were not
Applied. No Corrections For Beam Particle Losses
Were Applied.
1. The Overall Systematic Error in the Cross Section
Scale was 2.5% Containing Uncertainties in Target
Thickness (0.6%), Current Integration (1%), Detector
Efficiency (1 TO 2%).
2.   The  (NOT  LINEAR)  Error  in  the Energy Scale is
Delta-E(E)=12.5 MeV**2/E and 50 MeV**2/E For  Deuterons
And Alphas, Respectively.  The Losses of Beam Particles
Due to Reactions in the Target Amount Up to 5%, But
Were not Corrected.
Lakw
Some Corrections have Been Included by
CAJAD
Reaction Lines are Corrected. Data Headings
Are Changed.  Converted to Lower Case.
Last checking has been done.
Shielded
Stack Consisting of Al-Foils, Thickness 100 and 200
Micrometer, Purity 99.999%.  The Individual Thickness
Of Each Foil was Measured After Irradiation by Weighing
And Area Determination.
The Error Listed is the Statistical Error.
